# This file is entirely OPTIONAL — the app needs no API key. The catalogue is
# scraped from the official site (en.onepiece-cardgame.com); nothing here is
# required. Read automatically by the backend for local dev (`go run .`); real
# environment variables override anything set here.

# ---- Optional overrides ----
# Local defaults already work when you run `go run ./backend` from the repo root
# (db -> ./data/, catalogue -> ./catalogue.json). Paths are relative to the
# working directory. In Docker these come from the image instead.
# PORT=8080
# DB_PATH=./data/onepiece.db
# CATALOGUE_PATH=./catalogue.json

# ---- Startup auto-sync ----
# On startup the backend refreshes the catalogue from the official site in the
# background (the existing catalogue is served meanwhile; the UI shows a
# "Synchronisation de la base de données…" banner).
# SYNC_ON_START: set false to never auto-sync on boot (manual sync only).
# SYNC_MAX_AGE_HOURS: skip the startup sync if the catalogue is younger than
#   this many hours (avoids re-scraping on quick restarts). 0 = always sync.
# SYNC_ON_START=true
# SYNC_MAX_AGE_HOURS=24

# ---- Image proxy ----
# Card images are fetched server-side (their host blocks cross-origin <img>
# loads) and downscaled + re-encoded to JPEG before being served. The grid
# shows them ~220px wide, so the full-size source is wasteful.
# IMAGE_WIDTH: grid thumbnail width in px (height kept proportional, never
#   upscaled). Default 220 (the grid tile size). The click-to-zoom view always
#   requests the full-size source regardless of this setting.
# IMAGE_CACHE: when true, processed images are kept on disk so each card is
#   fetched and resized only once. Thumbnails and full-size images are cached
#   separately. Default false.
# IMAGE_CACHE_DIR: where to store them. Default ./data/imgcache.
# IMAGE_WIDTH=220
# IMAGE_CACHE=false
# IMAGE_CACHE_DIR=./data/imgcache
